54 /*
55  * DBG_LEVEL is used to control the log printed by DBG_BUFFER(), DBG_INDEX() and DBG_TEXT().
56  * LEVEL_OFF : Print None
57  * LEVEL_ERROR : Print ERROR
58  * LEVEL_WARN : Print ERROR, WARN
59  * LEVEL_INFO : Print ERROR, WARN, INFO
60  * LEVEL_TRACE : Print ERROR, WARN, INFO, TRACE
61  */
62 #define DBG_LEVEL LEVEL_TRACE

335 #define COMBINE_TRACE_INFO(type, subtype, module, level) (uint32_t)(((type)<<24) | ((subtype)<<16) | ((module)<<8) | (level))
336 
337 /* Internal macro that is wrapped by internal macro DBG_BUFFER. */
338 #define DBG_BUFFER_INTERNAL(type, sub_type, module, level, fmt, param_num, ...) do {\
339  static const char format[] TRACE_DATA = fmt;\
340  log_buffer(COMBINE_TRACE_INFO(type, sub_type, module, level), (uint32_t)format, param_num, ##__VA_ARGS__);\
341  } while (0)
342 
343 #if (DBG_LEVEL >= LEVEL_ERROR)
344 #define DBG_BUFFER_LEVEL_ERROR(type, sub_type, module, fmt, param_num, ...) do {\
345  DBG_BUFFER_INTERNAL(type, sub_type, module, LEVEL_ERROR, fmt, param_num, ##__VA_ARGS__);\
346  } while (0)
347 #define DBG_INDEX_LEVEL_ERROR(type, sub_type, module, fmt, param_num, ...) do {\
348  log_index(COMBINE_TRACE_INFO(type, sub_type, module, LEVEL_ERROR), fmt, param_num, ##__VA_ARGS__);\
349  } while (0)
350 #define DBG_TEXT_LEVEL_ERROR(type, sub_type, module, fmt, ...) do {\
351  log_text(COMBINE_TRACE_INFO(type, sub_type, module, LEVEL_ERROR), fmt, ##__VA_ARGS__);\
352  } while (0)
353 #else
354 #define DBG_BUFFER_LEVEL_ERROR(type, sub_type, module, fmt, param_num, ...)
355 #define DBG_INDEX_LEVEL_ERROR(type, sub_type, module, fmt, param_num, ...)
356 #define DBG_TEXT_LEVEL_ERROR(type, sub_type, module, fmt, ...)
357 #endif
